1) that is small, monomeric and noninteracting. As shown in Table
2, Ala has the highest side-chain α-helical propensity and Gly the lowest. A value for Pro could not be determined because the side-chain of this amino acid completely disrupts α-helical structure, even in the presence of helix inducing solvents such as trifluoroethanol (TFE). Such intrinsic propensity values provide a powerful tool for protein design as well as providing a guide to predicting the potential conformational status of a peptide during chromatography. The latter is particularly true of RP-HPLC because the nonpolar environment characteristic of this HPLC mode make it a strong inducer of α-helical structure in potentially α-helical amino acid sequences (12
–15).

