It should be noted that the greater the sample load, the sooner the appearance of desired peptide product eluted from the column, i.e., Fr. 54 for a 200-mg load vs Fr. 63 for a 100-mg load. In addition, the larger the load, the greater the number of fractions needed for product elution (13 fractions for the 100 mg load and 18 fractions for the 200-mg load).The RP-HPLC column has the capacity for an even larger sample load than 200 mg. However, there is not sufficient material available to determine the maximum load on this column.

